<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9853] ClassFormatError using method reference on interface target</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9853</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After upgrading to 3.0.7, using &lt;tt&gt;interfaceField::method&lt;/tt&gt; is resulting in bytecode output containing an InterfaceMethodref that looks as expected. When running it in the Eclipse JUnit runner, however (which I think is unimportant), I&apos;m getting a loading error from the JVM:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Caused by: java.lang.ClassFormatError: Invalid constant pool index 130 in &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;file com/example/sendgrid/SendgridMailSender (not a method)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where the offending constant is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&#160; #130 = InterfaceMethodref #126.#129&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// com/sendgrid/SendGridAPI.api:(Lcom/sendgrid/Request;)Lcom/sendgrid/Response;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from the 4.6.8 SendGrid SDK.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Compiling with 3.0.6 seems to work. Replacing &lt;tt&gt;::&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;.&amp;amp;&lt;/tt&gt; seems to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The JVM is 11.0.9-hs-adpt.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
